gdb setup:-
1)in parent coding folder create .gdbinit file:-
# ~/Desktop/coding/.gdbinit
set pagination off

define hook-stop
  echo \n--- locals ---\n
  info locals
  echo \n--- backtrace ---\n
  backtrace
  echo \n
end

2)tell gdb to trust that folder, in home folder do:-
# ~/.gdbinit
add-auto-load-safe-path /home/sugam/Desktop/coding/

3) each project specific folder get's it's own gdbinit, also add there path in ~/.gdbinit:-
    add-auto-load-safe-path /home/sugam/Desktop/coding/GradeManager/
~
// gdb commands:-
break main        # set breakpoint at main
break file.cpp:10 # set breakpoint at line 10
run               # start program
n                 # next — step over
s                 # step — step into
finish            # run until current function returns
continue          # run until next breakpoint
print s1          # print variable
info locals       # print all locals
backtrace         # show call stack
quit              # exit GDB
Enter             # repeat last command

